          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript is used for contemplation and study and is a treatise on Hindu philosophy from the Vedānta school. Thought to be part of the Kenopaniṣad and associated with the lineage of the Sāmaveda paṇḍits, it regards notions of the Self, as well as the implications of other philosophical questions. Written in 100 verses.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
